private int lowerBound(List<Integer> nums, int target) {
    int left = -1, right = nums.size();
    while (left + 1 < right) {
        int mid = (left + right) >>> 1;
        if (nums.get(mid) < target) {
            left = mid;
        } else {
            right = mid;
        }
    }
    return right;
}
```

This function works by performing a binary search on the sorted list. The left and right pointers are initialized to the first and last element of the list. The while loop continues until the left pointer is no longer greater than the right pointer. In each iteration of the loop, the middle element is compared with the target. If the middle element is less than the target, the left pointer is updated to mid. If the middle element is greater than or equal to the target, the right pointer is updated to mid. The right pointer is then returned as the insertion point for the target.

